examples.en: His face sharpened like the face of a sick man.
The lecture sharpened my understanding of the topic.
Make sure the nib has been sharpened before you try to cut anything.
The outlines of the mountains sharpened as we got closer.
The second baseman sharpened his spikes before every game.
The circumstances which pointed and sharpened the public feelings on that occasion.
Edge-tools are sharpened, by applying the basil to the convex surface of a grind-stone.
